  "prompt": "My pet cat scratched me accidentally.Its not vaccinated and I'm from India. 7 days have passed but the cat is fully well. Do I need anti-rabies shots?",
  "response": "Here's guidance for your situation:\n\n1. If the cat is your own pet and is showing no signs of illness, the rabies risk is lower.\n\n2. However, in India, where rabies is still prevalent, it's recommended to:\n- Consult a doctor immediately\n- Get medical evaluation of the wound\n- Discuss potential anti-rabies vaccination\n\n3. Key considerations:\n- Is the cat an indoor or outdoor cat?\n- Has it been in contact with other animals?\n- Are its vaccination status and origin known?\n\n4. General medical advice:\n- Clean the wound thoroughly\n- Seek professional medical consultation\n- Let a healthcare professional assess your specific risk\n\n5. Typical protocol in India:\n- Even with low-risk scenarios, doctors often recommend precautionary anti-rabies shots\n- A medical professional can best determine your specific need\n\nRecommendation: Visit a local doctor or hospital for professional medical advice tailored to your specific situation. Do not rely solely on online advice for such medical decisions.",
